some of the normal values listed in the following table were obtained from studies involving small number of subjects. The values should therefore have been considered as approximate and no deﬁnite clinical conclusions should be based on them. The adjustment of normal limits for age, sex, and environment which is also needed has been omitted here because of the limited sources of data.
